--How to Compile
    In HW2/src/, enter the following command:
    $ make
    An executable file "hw2" will be generated in "HW2/bin/".

    If you want to remove the compiled files, enter:
    $ make clean

--How to Run
    Usage:
    $ ../bin/hw2 <input_file> <output_file>

    E.g., in HW2/src/, run the program with:
    $ ../bin/hw2 ../testcase/public1.txt ../output/public1.out

--Automated Execution
    You can also use predefined make commands:
    (In HW2/src/)

    Run with a public test case (e.g., public1.txt):
    $ make run public1

    Verify the output for a public test case:
    $ make verify public1

    Run and verify in one step:
    $ make run_verify public1

    Run with the sample test case:
    $ make sample

# --Directory Structure
# HW2/
# │── bin/             # Compiled executable and object files
# │── output/          # Output files generated by the program
# │── src/             # Source code, Makefile, and README
# │   ├── Makefile     # Build script
# │   ├── README.md    # Instructions
# │   ├── *.cpp        # Source files
# │   ├── *.hpp        # Header files
# │── testcase/        # Input test cases
# │── verifier/        # Verification scripts
# │── .gitignore       # Git ignore file
